# ============================================
# INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================

# 1. Create a 'public' folder in your project root if it doesn't exist
# 2. Create two files: robots.txt and sitemap.xml
# 3. Copy the respective content above into each file
# 4. Replace "yourdomain.com" with your actual domain
# 5. Update lastmod dates when you make changes
# 6. Add new URLs as you create more pages/sections

# For Vite projects, files in 'public' folder are automatically 
# served at the root URL, so:
# - public/robots.txt → https://yourdomain.com/robots.txt
# - public/sitemap.xml → https://yourdomain.com/sitemap.xml

# ============================================
# SITEMAP PRIORITIES GUIDE
# ============================================

# 1.0 = Most important (Homepage)
# 0.9 = Very important (Main services, products)
# 0.8 = Important (About, Contact, Key pages)
# 0.7 = Moderately important (Team, Secondary pages)
# 0.6 = Less important (Blog posts, Articles)
# 0.5 = Least important (Archive, Old content)

# ============================================
# CHANGEFREQ GUIDE
# ============================================

# always  = Document changes every time it's accessed
# hourly  = Updates multiple times per day
# daily   = Updates once per day
# weekly  = Updates once per week (good for most pages)
# monthly = Updates once per month (good for static pages)
# yearly  = Rarely changes
# never   = Archived content